author: Ben
text:
I don‚Äôt even know what is possible this season anymore with Europe but all I know is that there is a massive change of attention and response needed at Stamford Bridge on Wednesday night. 

We can never make anything easy for ourselves can we‚Ä¶

#SOUARS #COYG #Arsenal

author: Ben
text:
Unfortunately, I knew it was coming from when we went 1-0 down! Turned to my Dad at about 60 minutes and just said that I don‚Äôt think we would score if we played another two halves of football on top of that! 

#SOUARS #COYG #Arsenal

author: Ben
text:
Spurs losing today gave us a brilliant opportunity to put it back into our own hands again but we throw it away and are now staring down a horrible run in after losing the so called ‚Äòeasier‚Äô games on that run in! 

I‚Äôm fuming if you couldn‚Äôt tell. 

#SOUARS #COYG #Arsenal

author: Ben
text:
Start Pepe upfront against Chelsea, try something different because Eddie will be completely shut out of the game with their back line! A massive response is needed but we threw away a brilliant chance to make up for the last couple of weeks today! 

#SOUARS #COYG #Arsenal

author: Ben
text:
I really am dreading the next three matches and especially the Bridge on Wednesday night! Need to seriously rethink our ideas and tactics because it‚Äôs not working against mid table sides so it isn‚Äôt going to suddenly work against the top sides! 

#SOUARS #COYG #Arsenal

author: Ben
text:
Look at Chelsea the other week. They lost 1-3 at home to Real Madrid and then came out against Southampton and absolutely smashed them 0-6 and it could‚Äôve been ten! That‚Äôs how you come back and show that you‚Äôre sorry for a performance! 

#SOUARS #COYG #Arsenal

author: Ben
text:
Also, I don‚Äôt want to hear the players for the third week running come out and apologise and say ‚Äúwe will learn and bounce back‚Äù because quite frankly it‚Äôs taking the piss! 

It‚Äôs an insult to the fans when you go and continue to perform like that! 

#SOUARS #COYG #Arsenal

author: Akeem musa
text: @ltarsenal But you failed to mention that club in your lamentatation.... Let me help you, #ARSENAL #ARSENAL

author: Ben
text:
At the rate we are going we will be lucky to get Europa League because the next three matches I wasn‚Äôt looking forward to anyway but now I‚Äôm dreading off the back of three straight league defeats! 

Can‚Äôt wait for the Bridge on Wednesday night! üò¨

#SOUARS #COYG #Arsenal

author: Ben
text:
I said in January when we didn‚Äôt sign a striker that it will come back to bite us and cost us top 4 which is exactly what it‚Äôs doing! No focal point upfront to play off! 

0 points from 9 available against Palace, Brighton & Southampton isn‚Äôt good enough!

#SOUARS #COYG #Arsenal

author: Ben
text:
Why didn‚Äôt we start Gabi or Pepe upfront today rather than Eddie? Eddie didn‚Äôt have an awful game but when we cross it into the box who on earth are we aiming it at! 

Nobody in there can win a header against these centre backs! 

#SOUARS #COYG #Arsenal

author: Ben
text:
The injuries have been unfortunate but we got the team selection wrong again today! Cedric brings nothing to the team and I would prefer White to go out there as a right back and bring Holding into the back line! 

#SOUARS #COYG #Arsenal

author: Ben
text:
The worst thing is that all three defeats have been against sides who have nothing to play for. Chelsea turned up and pumped six past this lot last week and we turn up and gift them a lovely three points! 

It‚Äôs honestly unacceptable! 

#SOUARS #COYG #Arsenal

author: Ben
text:
Even today, we created a couple of chances which Forster made some excellent saves from but spent most of the time with the ball on the edge of the area with no clue what to do! 

The season has well and truly fallen apart within 18 days.

#SOUARS #COYG #Arsenal

author: Ben
text:
THREAD:

I said when we lost at Crystal Palace that it was all about the response but these last three matches have been shocking. 

We have scored once in them games and it was a deflected shot from miles out! 

#SOUARS #COYG #Arsenal
